definition.value: A hydroxycoumarin antibiotic that is obtained from Streptomyces rishiriensis and exhibits potent antibacterial and anticancer activity.
An oxygen molecular entity that acts as an excellent buffer for many biological systems at near-neutral pH.
A member of the class of MOPS that is morpholine substituted by a 3-sulfonatopropyl group at the nitrogen atom.
An organic sodium salt which is the disodium salt of eosin b diphenol.
An analogue of PD173955 where the methylmercapto group is replaced by aminomethyl.
A member of the class of coumestans that is coumestan with hydroxy substituents at positions 3 and 9.
An analogue of vandetanib where the N-methylpiperidin-4-yl group is replaced by 4-aminomethyl.
An analogue of sunitinib in which the 2-(diethylamino)ethyl amide group is replaced by 3-aminopropyl.
An analogue of staurosporine where the N-methyl group is replaced by a long-chain acyl group.
An analogue of imatinib where the piperidine N-methyl group is replaced by 2-aminoethyl.
An analogue of gefitinib in which the morpholino group is replaced by NH2.
An analogue of pelitinib where the 4-(dimethylamino)but-2-enoyl group is replaced by 6-aminohexanoyl.
A racemic analogue of Ro 320-1195, where the terminal hydroxy group is replaced by an amino group.
Any sulfur oxoacid derivative derived from sulfurous acid.
The active insecticidal constituents of Chrysanthemum cinerariifolium flowers.
A trans-chrysanthemic acid in which both stereocentres have R configuration.
An ortho- and peri-fused polycyclic arene consisting of four fused benzene rings, resulting in a flat aromatic system.
An aminoquinoline that is 4-[(2,4-dichloro-5-methoxyphenyl)amino]-7-[3-(4-methylpiperazin-1-yl)propoxy]quinoline bearing additional cyano and methoxy substituents at positions 3 and 6 respectively.
